    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved level 1 vs. required level 2) is compensated by high specimen count (N=11), inter-laboratory replication, and the direct correspondence between the ASTM F1717 protocol and the clinical loading scenario. Overall credibility is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion for the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending COU.",
